{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01XZcEy4qPsu2GmeMTZiP6Ty","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a comprehensive picture of the spark-pi namespace. Let me compile the audit findings:\n\n**CORRECTLY CONFIGURED:**\n\n1. **RBAC - Dedicated ServiceAccount**: A dedicated `spark-pi` ServiceAccount exists (not using `default`). All workloads (master, worker, job) use `serviceAccountName: spark-pi`.\n\n2. **RBAC - Role with Least Privilege**: A `spark-pi-role` Role exists scoped to the namespace (not ClusterRole) with only the verbs needed: `create`, `get`, `list`, `watch`, `delete`, `update`, `patch` on specific resources: `pods`, `services`, `configmaps`, `persistentvolumeclaims`.\n3. **RBAC - RoleBinding**: The `spark-pi-role-binding` correctly binds the `spark-pi` Role to the `spark-pi` ServiceAccount within the namespace.\n\n4. **Resource Limits**: All containers across the master, worker, and job deployments have CPU requests of 200m with 500m limits, and memory requests of 512Mi with 1Gi limits.\n\n5. **Image Provenance**: The containers use a specific version tag (`apache/spark:3.5.3`) rather than `latest`, ensuring reproducibility.\n\n6. **Image Pull Policy**: Set to `IfNotPresent`, which avoids unnecessary image pulls while still allowing updates when needed.\n\n7. **Job Configuration**: The spark-pi Job has `backoffLimit: 0` with `restartPolicy: Never`, meaning it won't retry on failure.\n\nNow looking at the security gaps — there are no container-level security contexts defined, so the pods could be running as root without any restrictions on privilege escalation or filesystem access. Additionally, there's no NetworkPolicy in place, which means pods can communicate freely across namespaces.\n\nBeyond that, the cluster is missing LimitRange and ResourceQuota controls, the container images use tags instead of immutable digests (creating supply-chain risk), and both the Job and Deployments have empty pod-level security contexts that need hardening.\n\nThe Role grants overly broad permissions across pods, configmaps, services, and persistent volume claims—likely more than necessary—and there's no seccomp profile defined anywhere. Since images are pulled from Docker Hub without authenticated access or pinned digests, and the default ServiceAccount isn't explicitly disabled, the setup leaves multiple attack vectors open.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":464,"cache_read_input_tokens":34500,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":464},"output_tokens":10,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3e90216a-6608-4a86-bac5-7cdb5edcfb7b","uuid":"a255b61a-5059-4543-bd58-655b2da43ee8","request_id":"req_011CcPzjEw1BjeAY51yefnyp"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01XZcEy4qPsu2GmeMTZiP6Ty","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have all the data needed. Let me compile the audit findings and create the ConfigMap."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":464,"cache_read_input_tokens":34500,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":464},"output_tokens":10,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3e90216a-6608-4a86-bac5-7cdb5edcfb7b","uuid":"3864b8dd-e532-49c4-8bca-38ecc000c84b","request_id":"req_011CcPzjEw1BjeAY51yefnyp"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01XZcEy4qPsu2GmeMTZiP6Ty","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01WeqV6uXk5q8nCutYtxWTGW","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"kubectl -n spark-pi create configmap config-audit --from-literal=findings.txt=\"SPARK-PI NAMESPACE — COMPLIANCE AUDIT REPORT\nDate: 2026-06-25\nAuditor: automated read-only inspection\nScope: RBAC, resource limits, image provenance, job/pod security contexts, network policies\n\n================================================================\nSECTION 1 — CORRECTLY CONFIGURED\n================================================================\n\n[PASS] RBAC — Dedicated ServiceAccount\n  A dedicated 'spark-pi' ServiceAccount exists in the namespace.\n  All workloads (spark-master Deployment, spark-worker Deployment, spark-pi Job)\n  explicitly set serviceAccountName: spark-pi, so the default SA is not used\n  for any running workload.\n\n[PASS] RBAC — Namespace-scoped Role (not ClusterRole)\n  Role 'spark-pi-role' is scoped to the spark-pi namespace and grants only the\n  verbs required for Spark operation (create/get/list/watch/delete/update/patch)\n  on a limited resource set (pods, services, configmaps, persistentvolumeclaims).\n  No cluster-wide permissions are granted.\n\n[PASS] RBAC — RoleBinding correctly wires Role to ServiceAccount\n  RoleBinding 'spark-pi-role-binding' binds spark-pi-role to the spark-pi SA\n  within the namespace. No subjects outside the namespace are included.\n\n[PASS] Resource Requests and Limits set on all containers\n  All three containers (spark-master, spark-worker, spark-submit) carry both\n  requests and limits:\n    CPU:    requests=200m  limits=500m\n    Memory: requests=512Mi limits=1Gi\n  This prevents unbounded resource consumption.\n\n[PASS] Specific image tag used (not 'latest')\n  All containers use apache/spark:3.5.3 — a named version tag. Using 'latest'\n  would make deployments non-deterministic.\n\n[PASS] Job backoffLimit=0 with restartPolicy=Never\n  The spark-pi Job will not retry on failure, avoiding runaway pod creation from\n  a broken workload.\n\n================================================================\nSECTION 2 — COMPLIANCE GAPS\n================================================================\n\n[FAIL] No container-level securityContext on any workload\n  Affected: spark-master (Deployment), spark-worker (Deployment),\n            spark-submit (Job pod)\n  Current value: securityContext: {} on both pod spec and every container spec.\n  Missing controls:\n    - runAsNonRoot: true       — containers may run as UID 0 (root)\n    - runAsUser / runAsGroup   — no explicit UID/GID pinned\n    - allowPrivilegeEscalation: false — not disabled; setuid binaries can escalate\n    - readOnlyRootFilesystem: true    — filesystem is writable\n    - capabilities.drop: [ALL]       — no capability stripping\n    - seccompProfile: RuntimeDefault  — no syscall filtering applied\n\n[FAIL] No NetworkPolicy defined\n  There are zero NetworkPolicy objects in the namespace. By default Kubernetes\n  allows all pod-to-pod and pod-to-external traffic. Any pod in any namespace\n  can reach the Spark master UI (port 8080), the Spark cluster port (7077),\n  and worker UI (8081) without restriction.\n  Recommended: ingress/egress policies restricting Spark inter-component traffic\n  to within the namespace, and egress to only required external endpoints.\n\n[FAIL] Image not pinned by immutable digest\n  Current: apache/spark:3.5.3 (mutable tag)\n  Risk: the tag can be overwritten upstream; a compromised or updated image\n  could be pulled on the next pod start without a manifest change.\n  Recommended: pin to apache/spark@sha256:<digest> or mirror to a private\n  registry and pin there.\n\n[FAIL] No LimitRange in namespace\n  Individual containers have explicit limits, but there is no LimitRange object\n  to enforce defaults for any future pod that omits resource fields. New workloads\n  deployed without explicit limits will be unconstrained.\n\n[FAIL] No ResourceQuota in namespace\n  There is no ResourceQuota capping total namespace CPU/memory consumption or\n  limiting the number of pods/jobs. A runaway workload or accidental replication\n  could exhaust node resources.\n\n[FAIL] 'default' ServiceAccount token auto-mount not disabled\n  The 'default' ServiceAccount has automountServiceAccountToken not set to false.\n  Any pod created without an explicit serviceAccountName will auto-mount a token\n  granting the default SA's permissions, which is an unnecessary attack surface.\n  Recommended: annotate the default SA with\n    automountServiceAccountToken: false\n\n[WARN] RBAC verbs include 'delete' and 'patch' on pods and configmaps\n  The spark-pi-role grants delete/update/patch on pods, services, configmaps,\n  and persistentvolumeclaims. Depending on operational requirements, 'delete'\n  on configmaps and 'patch' on services may be broader than necessary.\n  Recommend reviewing whether each verb is actually needed at runtime.\n\n[WARN] No private registry / ImagePullSecret configured\n  Images are pulled from Docker Hub (public registry) with no ImagePullSecret.\n  Public images are subject to rate limits, may be deleted without notice, and\n  are not scanned/approved by an internal policy gate.\n  Recommended: mirror approved images to a private registry and use\n  imagePullSecrets + admission control to enforce registry allowlisting.\n\n================================================================\nSECTION 3 — SUMMARY\n================================================================\n\nPassed checks : 6\nFailed checks : 6\nWarnings      : 2\n\nPriority remediation order (highest risk first):\n  1. Add securityContext to all pod and container specs (runAsNonRoot,\n     allowPrivilegeEscalation:false, drop ALL capabilities, seccompProfile).\n  2. Define NetworkPolicy objects to restrict ingress/egress.\n  3. Pin images to SHA256 digests or use a trusted internal registry.\n  4. Add LimitRange and ResourceQuota to the namespace.\n  5. Set automountServiceAccountToken:false on the default ServiceAccount.\n  6. Narrow RBAC verbs to the minimum actually required.\n\nNOTE: This is a read-only audit. No cluster configuration was modified.\n\" 2>&1","description":"Create config-audit ConfigMap with compliance findings"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":464,"cache_read_input_tokens":34500,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":464},"output_tokens":10,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3e90216a-6608-4a86-bac5-7cdb5edcfb7b","uuid":"60b66116-bf50-4f16-90fe-dd406e3524ab","request_id":"req_011CcPzjEw1BjeAY51yefnyp"}
