{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Vwf6Na5hDqzMv4HJZbNHwL","type":"tool_result","content":"SPARK-PI NAMESPACE — COMPLIANCE AUDIT REPORT\nDate: 2026-06-25\nAuditor: automated read-only inspection\nScope: RBAC, resource limits, image provenance, job/pod security contexts, network policies\n\n================================================================\nSECTION 1 — CORRECTLY CONFIGURED\n================================================================\n\n[PASS] RBAC — Dedicated ServiceAccount\n  A dedicated 'spark-pi' ServiceAccount exists in the namespace.\n  All workloads (spark-master Deployment, spark-worker Deployment, spark-pi Job)\n  explicitly set serviceAccountName: spark-pi, so the default SA is not used\n  for any running workload.\n\n[PASS] RBAC — Namespace-scoped Role (not ClusterRole)\n  Role 'spark-pi-role' is scoped to the spark-pi namespace and grants only the\n  verbs required for Spark operation (create/get/list/watch/delete/update/patch)\n  on a limited resource set (pods, services, configmaps, persistentvolumeclaims).\n  No cluster-wide permissions are granted.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3e90216a-6608-4a86-bac5-7cdb5edcfb7b","uuid":"fa07035d-f52b-4882-bd51-43d03f98a869","timestamp":"2026-06-25T12:43:01.498Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"SPARK-PI NAMESPACE — COMPLIANCE AUDIT REPORT\nDate: 2026-06-25\nAuditor: automated read-only inspection\nScope: RBAC, resource limits, image provenance, job/pod security contexts, network policies\n\n================================================================\nSECTION 1 — CORRECTLY CONFIGURED\n================================================================\n\n[PASS] RBAC — Dedicated ServiceAccount\n  A dedicated 'spark-pi' ServiceAccount exists in the namespace.\n  All workloads (spark-master Deployment, spark-worker Deployment, spark-pi Job)\n  explicitly set serviceAccountName: spark-pi, so the default SA is not used\n  for any running workload.\n\n[PASS] RBAC — Namespace-scoped Role (not ClusterRole)\n  Role 'spark-pi-role' is scoped to the spark-pi namespace and grants only the\n  verbs required for Spark operation (create/get/list/watch/delete/update/patch)\n  on a limited resource set (pods, services, configmaps, persistentvolumeclaims).\n  No cluster-wide permissions are granted.","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
